<TITLE> Over 100 BDR men brought to Dhaka for grilling </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 12 (bdnews24.com)Over 100 BDR members were brought to the border force's headquarters in the capital from Jessore, Satkhira and Naogoan battalions on Sunday for interrogation, without showing them arrested. The border guards reported to their battalions, as ordered by the government, after the Feb. 25-26 mutiny at the BDR headquarters in Dhaka. Police brought 57 BDR members to the Peelkhana headquarters from Jhumjhumpur 22 Rifles Battalion. Some 59 BDR members reported back for duty to Jhumjhumpur in the aftermath of the mutiny. Two of them were brought to Dhaka earlier. Jessore Kotwali police officer-in-charge Abul Bashar told bdnews24.com the border guards were taken to Dhaka as their connection with the mutiny "was proved through video footage and statements by BDR men in detention". "None of the 57 has been shown arrested," he added. Thirteen members of Satkhira 41 Rifles Battalion were brought to Dhaka. Two of them were taken to headquarters earlier, as a total of 15 had reported back to 41 Rifles after the mutiny, Satkhira superintendent of police Abu Sufian told bdnews24.com. Thirty-two BDR members and a nurse from Naogaon 43 and 46 Rifles Battalions were also brought to Dhaka on Sunday. bdnews24
